The Web Applications Working Group invites implementation of the Candidate Recommendation of Web Storage (Second Edition). This specification defines an API for persistent data storage of key-value pair data in Web clients, and introduces two related mechanisms, similar to HTTP session cookies, for storing name-value pairs on the client side. Learn more about the Rich [&#8230;]<img src="https://www.w3.org/analytics/piwik/piwik.php?idsite=7&amp;rec=1&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Farchives%2F4751%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dw3c-invites-implementations-of-web-storage-second-edition&amp;action_name=W3C+Invites+Implementations+of+Web+Storage+%28Second+Edition%29&amp;urlref=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2Fblog%2Fnews%2Ffeed" style="border:0;width:0;height:0" width="0" height="0" alt="" />
